I added a bool variable isUsed to tell if a key was already added to the keys array and included this as additional if condition to be met. I've also split the if statement to 4 ones, as it was too unreadable for me. The solution below if anyone needed that:

```
constructor() {
      this.keys = [];

      // Add WSAD input to keys on press
      window.addEventListener('keydown', e => {

        let isUsed = false;

        if (e.key === 'w' && isUsed == false && this.keys.indexOf(e.key) === -1) {
          this.keys.push(e.key);
          isUsed = true;
        }
        
        if (e.key === 's' && isUsed == false && this.keys.indexOf(e.key) === -1) {
          this.keys.push(e.key);
          isUsed = true;
        }
        
        if (e.key === 'a' && isUsed == false && this.keys.indexOf(e.key) === -1) {
          this.keys.push(e.key);
          isUsed = true;
        }
        
        if (e.key === 'd' && isUsed == false && this.keys.indexOf(e.key) === -1) {
          this.keys.push(e.key);
          isUsed = true;
        }

        console.log(e.key, this.keys);
      });
    }
```

Also note you can only press 3 keys at once like this in Brave (and most of the browsers which are basing on Chromium engine most likely)

